						<summary>

						<p>On the north face of the north pillar of the rock-cut shrine, Mēlaikkōyil temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 7(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold <hi rend="italic">(tuḷaippoṉ)</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp for god in the temple of Tirumūlaṭṭānattu-perumānaḍigaḷ at Tirunalakkuṉṟam in Kuṉṟiyūr-nāḍu by Naṅgai-Naldēviyār, wife of Sembiyaṉ Irukkuvēḷār.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 241. </p>						

